#Hey Fabian, I have attached the raw data values obtained from my calibration test. Just to give you a short description as to how the values were obtained: the sensor checked the values at 10 min increments, and the sample size observed were at the 90 min - 150 min time points (this is the n= 7 sample size) since that's when equilibrium should occur within the microenvironment. I averaged that sample size of observed values and compared it to the reference relative humidity of both salt type (NaCl and MgC) at 25C (room temp). I calculated the error between the average observed value and reference relative humidity of the each corresponding salt, along with the root mean squared error considering n=7.

#Values found in literature as averages. https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/e796/6abb5a91dad655a4de69ea5c80db9d032b59.pdf

NaCl.lit.T <- c(0,5,10,15,20,25,30,35,40,45,50)
